WEBVTT

00:01.240 --> 00:02.880
TOMMY: <i>I just got served
a black hand.</i>

00:02.960 --> 00:05.800
JOHN: <i>Everybody will have got one.
They're coming for us all.</i>

00:05.880 --> 00:07.280
TOMMY: <i>These men will
not leave our city</i>

00:07.360 --> 00:08.600
<i>until the whole family is dead.</i>

00:08.680 --> 00:11.920
ARTHUR: <i>This was all my fault.
It was me that shot the old man.</i>

00:12.000 --> 00:13.680
John's dead because of me.

00:14.320 --> 00:16.080
TOMMY: <i>Within a four.mile radius
of the Garrison</i>

00:16.160 --> 00:18.000
<i>every man is a guard
and a soldier for us.</i>

00:18.080 --> 00:20.760
<i>We're going back.
Back to Small Heath.</i>

00:20.840 --> 00:23.120
<i>That's how it works. An eye for an eye.</i>

00:23.200 --> 00:24.520
<i>It's called vendetta.</i>

00:24.600 --> 00:28.360
We are an organisation,
but different. Imagine...

00:28.440 --> 00:30.480
<i>None of you will survive.</i>

00:30.560 --> 00:34.880
JESSIE: <i>And how is Tommy Shelby OBE,
going to stop a revolution?</i>

00:34.960 --> 00:36.480
TOMMY: <i>lf I get Jessie Eden's trust,</i>

00:36.560 --> 00:38.720
<i>she gives me the names
of the instigators,</i>

00:38.800 --> 00:40.440
<i>I'll give them up to the Crown forces.</i>

00:40.520 --> 00:43.600
ABERAMA: <i>I want you to help my son
achieve his ambition.</i>

00:43.680 --> 00:45.160
You're a Peaky Blinder now, son.

00:45.240 --> 00:47.880
<i>We control him,
run the book, control the odds.</i>

00:47.960 --> 00:49.400
<i>We got a lot going on, that's all.</i>

00:49.480 --> 00:51.160
So it might be a good time
to get around?

00:51.240 --> 00:52.720
Mr Shelby will give you a 20% cut

00:52.800 --> 00:55.640
if you put Goliath down
in the fourth round.

00:55.720 --> 00:57.520
LUCA: So you're gonna take my boys

00:57.640 --> 01:00.000
and you're gonna bring them
to the ring as seconds.

01:00.080 --> 01:02.600
ALFIE: Yeah, Tommy Shelby
was right about you. Wasn't he?

01:02.880 --> 01:04.920
(SPEAKING YIDDISH)

01:11.600 --> 01:13.600
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

01:22.320 --> 01:25.800
<i># Take a walk to
the edge of town</i>

01:25.880 --> 01:28.880
<i># And go across the tracks</i>

01:31.120 --> 01:33.720
<i># Where the viaduct looms</i>

01:33.800 --> 01:35.880
<i># Like a bird of doom</i>

01:35.960 --> 01:40.240
<i># As it shifts and cracks</i>

01:41.280 --> 01:46.120
<i># Where secrets lie
in the border fires</i>

01:46.200 --> 01:48.720
<i># In the humming wires</i>

01:48.800 --> 01:52.520
<i># Hey man, you're never coming back</i>

01:52.600 --> 01:55.000
<i># Past the square, past the bridge</i>

01:55.080 --> 01:58.840
<i># Past the mills, past the stacks</i>

02:01.440 --> 02:06.480
<i># On a gathering storm
comes a tall handsome man</i>

02:06.560 --> 02:12.560
<i># In a dusty black coat
with a red right hand</i>

02:16.040 --> 02:19.160
<i># A red right hand</i>

02:20.760 --> 02:24.400
<i># With a red right hand #</i>

02:27.240 --> 02:29.240
(CROWD CHEERING)

02:45.360 --> 02:46.640
(GRUNTS)

02:48.880 --> 02:50.560
Yeah, you're like me, Tommy,

02:50.640 --> 02:53.600
you can't bear to watch a fight
which has got rules.

02:57.120 --> 02:58.680
Tommy, right, imagine...

02:59.920 --> 03:02.280
Imagine that you could not see.

03:04.000 --> 03:07.080
At all, you was born blind.

03:08.240 --> 03:12.280
Then one day you open up your eyes

03:13.040 --> 03:16.640
and you can see everything

03:17.240 --> 03:18.520
in the world.

03:19.760 --> 03:21.640
When before you could only

03:22.400 --> 03:24.400
touch it or smell it.

03:24.480 --> 03:26.680
Hmm. There it is.

03:28.440 --> 03:29.760
The revelation.

03:30.680 --> 03:31.680
Innit?

03:35.600 --> 03:36.920
I've had one.

03:38.720 --> 03:41.320
Yeah, saw a beautiful house
down in Margate.

03:41.400 --> 03:43.640
Great big white building...

03:44.400 --> 03:47.520
Monkey puzzle tree
against the sky blue.

03:48.720 --> 03:50.680
Beautiful. A piece of heaven.

03:50.760 --> 03:55.720
Actually, you see, the way the Earth,
it curves, I thought to myself,

03:55.800 --> 03:58.760
"Alfie, what are you doing?

04:00.840 --> 04:02.560
"What are you doing?

04:02.640 --> 04:05.800
"Why don't you just sell
every ounce of gold and sell

04:05.880 --> 04:09.640
"every barrel of rum you got and just
buy yourself some time, mate?"

04:12.800 --> 04:15.360
I need to buy myself some time.

04:17.000 --> 04:18.320
You're moving to Margate?

04:18.400 --> 04:21.680
I am actually, yeah.
I need to get myself some rest.

04:21.760 --> 04:23.240
I need some rest.

04:24.280 --> 04:26.320
Plus, the Americans are
here now, aren't they?

04:26.400 --> 04:28.240
So, that's it.

04:28.320 --> 04:32.000
Yeah. It's been that way ever since
the war, innit? The Americans.

04:33.600 --> 04:37.720
Big fucks small.

04:39.080 --> 04:40.840
Always, actually.

04:41.200 --> 04:42.280
Hmm?

04:42.800 --> 04:48.560
And there is a fight going on,
out there, between big and small.

04:50.840 --> 04:54.440
Big will fuck small.

04:58.920 --> 05:03.440
Right. Margate then. Blue skies, heaven.

05:07.760 --> 05:09.680
I will see you, Tommy.

05:11.560 --> 05:13.000
Might appear.

05:15.560 --> 05:17.440
Stay and watch the fight, Alfie?

05:18.680 --> 05:20.040
No, you're all right.

05:21.360 --> 05:23.360
I already know who wins.

05:24.120 --> 05:25.120
Don't I?

05:33.320 --> 05:34.320
Cheer up.

05:41.200 --> 05:42.760
(MAN SHOUTING)

05:47.400 --> 05:48.400
(BELL RINGS)

05:49.480 --> 05:51.640
MAN: Round one!

05:51.720 --> 05:53.080
(CROWD CLAMOURING)

05:56.320 --> 05:57.320
Left, right.

06:08.480 --> 06:09.480
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

06:15.040 --> 06:16.240
(GRUNTING)

06:16.320 --> 06:18.120
(YELLING)

06:19.760 --> 06:20.760
(GRUNTS)

06:21.400 --> 06:22.400
(CROWD CHEERING)

06:28.240 --> 06:30.200
-CROWD: Oh!
-(BELL RINGING)

06:31.760 --> 06:33.200
Bonnie! Bonnie!

06:33.800 --> 06:34.800
(SPEAKING ROMANI)

06:42.720 --> 06:44.840
I know he's a big bastard
but you got to...

06:44.920 --> 06:47.280
-Where's Solomons?
-Apparently he doesn't watch.

06:47.800 --> 06:49.320
Look at that corner. Look.

06:49.400 --> 06:51.440
The men there,
they don't know fighters.

06:51.520 --> 06:53.120
I don't like it.

06:53.200 --> 06:55.440
You feel it though, Tom, don't ya?

06:55.520 --> 06:57.400
I feel it. We're all right.

06:57.480 --> 06:59.440
We're surrounded by soldiers, Arthur.

06:59.520 --> 07:02.120
Alfie's men were strip searched.
We're all right.

07:03.640 --> 07:05.760
Right, come on, Gypsy boy, let's go.

07:05.840 --> 07:07.240
-(CHEERING)
-Round two!

07:08.920 --> 07:10.400
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

07:15.120 --> 07:16.880
(GRUNTING)

07:19.280 --> 07:20.280
(DOOR OPENS)

07:29.480 --> 07:31.800
POLLY: So what did Tommy say
when you told him?

07:33.080 --> 07:35.120
He said I'd get a weekly allowance.

07:35.200 --> 07:36.760
POLLY: Oh, he can be romantic.

07:36.880 --> 07:38.120
(DOOR OPENS)

07:39.360 --> 07:41.080
Course as company treasurer,

07:41.160 --> 07:43.240
I shall be questioning that expense.

07:43.320 --> 07:46.400
He said something like, "We've had
enough death, let's have some life."

07:46.480 --> 07:48.240
-(DOOR OPENS)
-Poll...

07:49.360 --> 07:51.200
This fight is fixed, isn't it?

07:51.960 --> 07:53.920
Poor Gypsy boy's getting
battered out there.

07:54.560 --> 07:56.720
Right. You said you have some news?

07:56.800 --> 07:58.440
Lizzie has some news.

07:58.520 --> 07:59.520
Polly.

07:59.600 --> 08:01.320
Well, tell her. Now!

08:01.400 --> 08:03.080
While the men are screaming for blood.

08:03.840 --> 08:06.000
Have a swig. You're gonna need it.

08:07.880 --> 08:10.000
I'm up the duff.

08:11.120 --> 08:12.800
And it's Tommy's.

08:13.960 --> 08:15.400
How far gone are you?

08:15.480 --> 08:17.520
If I were going to London
I'd be in Coventry.

08:17.600 --> 08:19.400
And are you carrying on past Coventry?

08:19.480 --> 08:21.200
All the way to fucking
Piccadilly Circus.

08:21.280 --> 08:23.240
You found out whether
she's having a boy or a girl, Poll?

08:23.320 --> 08:24.320
No.

08:24.440 --> 08:25.480
Go on then.

08:32.560 --> 08:33.560
(GIGGLING)

08:35.480 --> 08:36.480
It's a girl.

08:38.360 --> 08:39.440
Call her Ruby.

08:40.080 --> 08:41.280
Ruby Shelby.

08:42.000 --> 08:44.600
She'll be a star in a Hollywood movie.

08:45.840 --> 08:46.840
Hmm.

08:47.920 --> 08:50.480
-Congratulations.
-(DOOR OPENS)

08:50.560 --> 08:51.560
(CROWD CHEERING IN DISTANCE)

08:52.440 --> 08:53.560
Hey, Linda.

08:53.640 --> 08:57.360
Welcome to the extraordinary general
meeting of the Shelby ladies club.

08:57.440 --> 08:58.440
(ALL LAUGHING)

08:59.320 --> 09:00.600
Is there spit on my back?

09:01.440 --> 09:04.360
There were men out there spitting.
It's fucking disgusting.

09:04.440 --> 09:06.680
No, there's no spit on your back.

09:08.320 --> 09:10.920
Don't let us stop you doing
what you came in to do.

09:12.600 --> 09:13.600
What?

09:14.880 --> 09:18.280
It's helped me get through the fucking
nightmare of being stuck in this city.

09:19.800 --> 09:23.440
Well, since you're here
and you're almost family,

09:23.520 --> 09:24.760
Lizzie's got some news.

09:25.160 --> 09:27.440
-I'm pregnant.
-Oh?

09:28.600 --> 09:31.240
And who's the father, have you
managed to narrow it down?

09:33.000 --> 09:34.000
(SNORTING)

09:35.960 --> 09:37.680
Yes, it's Tommy.

09:38.360 --> 09:39.680
Congratulations.

09:40.200 --> 09:41.760
You've won the raffle at last.

09:42.640 --> 09:45.240
Yeah. She's a real
Shelby lady now, Linda.

09:46.280 --> 09:47.520
Just like you.

09:48.160 --> 09:51.120
Right, ladies,
let's rejoin our gentlemen.

09:51.680 --> 09:53.400
And just remember, Linda,

09:53.480 --> 09:56.240
if they spit, just spit back.

09:56.320 --> 09:57.760
(CHUCKLING)

09:59.480 --> 10:01.640
-I'll see you out there.
-All right.

10:02.960 --> 10:04.400
(CROWD CLAMOURING)

10:06.160 --> 10:07.480
Come on, Bonnie!

10:10.000 --> 10:11.000
(CHEERING)

10:13.240 --> 10:14.600
Put him away!

10:20.920 --> 10:23.440
Right. Who's with me, boys?

10:25.680 --> 10:28.320
Come get your loyalty, boy.

10:28.680 --> 10:30.280
You still in control, Bonnie?

10:30.880 --> 10:31.880
Yes.

10:32.680 --> 10:33.680
Then take him.

10:35.240 --> 10:36.760
(SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

10:37.160 --> 10:38.760
I give ya two to one!

10:39.080 --> 10:42.320
On the big Cockney Goliath, here.

10:42.400 --> 10:44.200
Take it or leave it, boys.

10:44.280 --> 10:46.120
Take it or leave it, boys.

10:46.200 --> 10:48.760
Two to one! Two to one!

10:49.600 --> 10:51.480
Look at them men in his corner. Look.

10:53.240 --> 10:54.880
They don't know fighters.

10:54.960 --> 10:56.800
They don't know the fucking ropes.

10:56.880 --> 10:59.400
It's the pills and the booze
spooking you, Arthur.

11:00.480 --> 11:01.840
-(CHEERING)
-Round three!

11:07.880 --> 11:08.960
(INAUDIBLE)

11:09.040 --> 11:12.640
Ah, look at them. They don't
stand right. They don't move right.

11:12.720 --> 11:15.000
They don't even care
if he fucking wins.

11:17.040 --> 11:18.480
It's the fucking pills, brother.

11:18.600 --> 11:19.680
All right?

11:30.320 --> 11:33.520
Come on, Bonnie!

11:37.360 --> 11:38.560
(ALL SHOUTING)

11:44.280 --> 11:46.480
Whoo! Come on, Bonnie!

11:46.920 --> 11:48.400
What the fuck are they laughing at?

11:49.680 --> 11:50.920
ARTHUR: Send her back.

11:51.400 --> 11:52.400
Too strong.

11:54.520 --> 11:55.520
POLLY: Come on, Bonnie!

11:55.800 --> 11:57.960
(ALL SHOUTING)

11:58.080 --> 11:59.080
(SNIFFS)

12:02.680 --> 12:03.680
(CROWD SHOUTING)

12:05.480 --> 12:07.480
TOMMY: Arthur, leave it.
ARTHUR: Where is he going?

12:07.560 --> 12:10.000
Sit down and watch
the fight, eh, Arthur!

12:10.080 --> 12:11.280
Come here!

12:11.360 --> 12:13.640
Let me do my fucking job!

12:14.160 --> 12:15.960
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

12:19.920 --> 12:20.920
(SNIFFS)

12:22.360 --> 12:23.360
(GRUNTS)

13:01.360 --> 13:02.640
(CHEERING)

13:06.000 --> 13:07.120
Bonnie!

13:07.200 --> 13:09.160
Bonnie! Are you okay?

13:14.880 --> 13:18.280
I'll give you two to one
now on the Cockney.

13:18.520 --> 13:19.520
(CLAMOURING)

13:24.600 --> 13:26.040
Right.

13:27.600 --> 13:28.600
(EXHALES SLOWLY)

13:44.200 --> 13:46.120
MAN: That's it. One, two. One, two!

13:52.480 --> 13:53.480
(CHEERING)

13:54.120 --> 13:55.960
Come on, Bonnie boy!

13:56.040 --> 13:57.920
Bonnie, come on, get him!

14:11.480 --> 14:12.800
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

14:18.040 --> 14:19.040
Come on!

14:19.560 --> 14:21.280
Where are Tommy and Arthur?

14:21.680 --> 14:23.000
MAN: Punch him!

14:23.080 --> 14:24.080
I don't know.

14:25.960 --> 14:27.120
Come on, Bonnie!

14:27.680 --> 14:29.160
Come on!

14:35.280 --> 14:36.600
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

14:55.680 --> 14:56.680
Arthur!

15:09.880 --> 15:11.200
(GRUNTING)

15:25.600 --> 15:28.160
(GROANING)
You fucking bastard.

15:30.440 --> 15:31.440
(GROANS)

15:45.800 --> 15:47.400
(PANTING)

15:52.520 --> 15:53.680
(GUNSHOT)

15:56.800 --> 15:58.200
Arthur!

17:16.520 --> 17:17.520
(YELLS)

17:31.520 --> 17:32.520
(INAUDIBLE)

17:33.240 --> 17:36.680
REFEREE: I declare Bonnie Gold the new
welterweight champion...

17:36.760 --> 17:40.040
of the Midlands South...

17:40.120 --> 17:41.120
Yes!

17:41.600 --> 17:44.120
Yes! Bonnie!

17:44.240 --> 17:45.640
Tommy, what's happened?

17:46.720 --> 17:47.920
Arthur's dead.

17:48.000 --> 17:50.040
(PANTING) He's dead.

17:52.160 --> 17:53.160
(INAUDIBLE)

17:55.520 --> 17:56.920
(CHEERING)

18:03.720 --> 18:05.920
Tommy, we have the other wop.

18:06.000 --> 18:07.680
Cunt had a wire in his pockets.

18:09.320 --> 18:10.320
(GRUNTS)

18:17.080 --> 18:18.200
Go on, Finn!

18:19.840 --> 18:20.840
Go on, Finn!

18:20.960 --> 18:22.160
(GROANING)

18:24.080 --> 18:25.440
Take his eyes, Finn.

18:26.360 --> 18:27.480
Do it for Arthur.

18:29.800 --> 18:31.560
Take his fucking eyes!

18:35.400 --> 18:36.880
No. No!

18:40.120 --> 18:41.120
(MAN SCREAMING)

18:57.240 --> 18:58.800
Close the doors!

18:59.760 --> 19:01.880
No one fucking leaves!

19:03.240 --> 19:05.120
(GUNSHOTS)

19:11.160 --> 19:12.560
My brother is dead.

19:15.560 --> 19:17.360
You hear me!

19:17.440 --> 19:20.240
My brother is dead!

19:21.080 --> 19:22.760
(PANTING)

19:35.960 --> 19:37.360
Tommy.

20:05.240 --> 20:06.840
(HORSE NEIGHING)

21:15.920 --> 21:17.640
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

21:25.880 --> 21:26.880
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

21:29.960 --> 21:31.120
Hello, Michael.

21:31.960 --> 21:33.480
There's been a change of plan.

21:34.440 --> 21:35.840
<i>Mr Gold will come and get you.</i>

21:37.040 --> 21:38.040
Arthur's dead.

21:48.600 --> 21:49.600
(DOOR CLOSES)

22:04.960 --> 22:06.640
Tommy, I've been trying to
think of words...

22:06.720 --> 22:07.720
Don't.

22:09.960 --> 22:11.320
Words don't work.

22:13.560 --> 22:15.960
Michael, we're in a grave situation.

22:16.760 --> 22:17.960
Tommy has a plan.

22:19.520 --> 22:21.200
Instead of going to Australia,

22:21.640 --> 22:22.840
you're going to New York.

22:27.040 --> 22:28.040
Why?

22:28.960 --> 22:31.720
'Cause the company has business
to attend to in America.

22:35.400 --> 22:36.640
Will I be coming back?

22:39.600 --> 22:41.040
Train leaves in an hour, Michael.

22:46.240 --> 22:47.440
You made a choice.

22:49.600 --> 22:51.080
You knew I was gonna be shot

22:52.480 --> 22:53.960
and you chose not to tell me.

22:56.960 --> 22:58.240
I chose my mum.

23:01.440 --> 23:03.200
When all this business is over

23:03.960 --> 23:06.240
we'll all be free to make
our own choices.

23:11.040 --> 23:12.040
So is that it?

23:17.000 --> 23:20.360
You get the train to Liverpool then
the <i>SS Monroe.</i> (CLEARS THROAT)

23:21.840 --> 23:23.120
Boat sails tomorrow.

23:27.200 --> 23:28.200
Now you can go.

24:03.440 --> 24:04.440
(SIGHS)

24:22.360 --> 24:24.120
I need an overseas connection, please.

24:25.560 --> 24:26.560
USA.

24:29.240 --> 24:30.240
(INHALES SLOWLY)

24:58.680 --> 25:00.920
-MAN: Tommy!
-It's all right, let her come.

25:11.000 --> 25:12.000
Please.

25:13.400 --> 25:14.680
Once we're all finished.

25:30.800 --> 25:31.800
(LIGHTER FLICKS)

25:32.600 --> 25:33.600
(FIRE BURNING)

25:34.000 --> 25:37.080
AUDREY: <i>Your note talked about
making terms for peace.</i>

25:37.840 --> 25:40.480
But my son says there are no terms.

25:42.800 --> 25:45.440
You took my husband and my son.

25:46.760 --> 25:48.440
We took two of your brothers.

25:52.000 --> 25:53.400
The vendetta is done.

25:53.480 --> 25:56.360
We say the vendetta is won.

25:57.320 --> 25:59.640
We will take everything you have.

26:00.640 --> 26:02.400
All your businesses,

26:02.480 --> 26:03.920
signed over to us.

26:05.400 --> 26:06.840
You agree to this.

26:08.080 --> 26:10.720
Or my son will kill you all.

26:11.800 --> 26:13.560
One by one.

26:14.960 --> 26:16.400
The vendetta is won.

26:18.000 --> 26:19.000
That's it.

26:21.480 --> 26:22.480
No more killing.

26:25.320 --> 26:29.400
Who do you think you were, Mr Shelby?

26:33.560 --> 26:36.440
(BANGING)

26:37.520 --> 26:38.520
(DOOR UNLOCKS)

26:57.160 --> 26:59.720
Why don't you let him know
we're hereto buy his business?

27:00.200 --> 27:01.520
Mr Solomons!

27:02.360 --> 27:04.640
Mr Changretta's here to see you!

27:12.280 --> 27:13.280
Come now.

27:16.080 --> 27:17.200
My Peaky!

27:18.560 --> 27:19.560
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

27:22.120 --> 27:23.600
They say he was a captain.

27:24.080 --> 27:25.080
Oh, yeah?

27:25.760 --> 27:28.400
Then you might wanna tell them
not to open that fucking door.

27:40.960 --> 27:44.080
LUCA: Seems Mr Solomons
already left town.

27:45.920 --> 27:47.560
So all this is mine.

27:48.200 --> 27:49.800
(LAUGHING)

27:53.840 --> 27:54.840
Huh.

28:19.960 --> 28:20.960
(DOOR OPENS)

28:22.520 --> 28:23.520
You don't knock?

28:24.240 --> 28:25.760
You don't know my new address?

28:25.840 --> 28:27.160
Hello, Lizzie, how are you?

28:27.240 --> 28:28.560
I know your new address, Lizzie,

28:28.640 --> 28:30.480
because it was me who bought you
the new fucking house.

28:30.560 --> 28:32.000
Then why don't you visit it?

28:43.960 --> 28:44.960
(DRAWER CLOSES)

28:46.480 --> 28:47.680
We have been busy.

28:49.280 --> 28:50.520
Busy doing what?

28:55.000 --> 28:56.240
Preparing for tomorrow.

28:57.200 --> 28:58.440
Why, what's tomorrow?

28:59.640 --> 29:02.840
Luca Changretta is coming to Birmingham.
It's our turn.

29:02.920 --> 29:05.840
He's already taken over
Alfie Solomons, Sabini,

29:05.920 --> 29:08.120
Titanics... All of them.

29:10.080 --> 29:13.520
And now he's coming to take control
of Shelby Company Limited.

29:16.480 --> 29:18.240
What are we going to do about that?

29:20.160 --> 29:21.760
We're gonna let him have it.

29:53.360 --> 29:54.720
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

30:17.600 --> 30:19.960
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

30:23.480 --> 30:26.840
All that's left of the Peaky
fucking Blinders.

30:48.880 --> 30:52.760
I've had my lawyer draw up these papers.

30:54.600 --> 30:58.760
Cover, uh, every enterprise
in your possession.

31:00.880 --> 31:04.080
Bars, restaurants, warehouses.

31:06.800 --> 31:12.000
Every fucking thing that you've taken
all these years to gather together.

31:15.600 --> 31:17.240
You will sign them all over

31:18.920 --> 31:20.240
to my family

31:24.280 --> 31:25.680
or you're gonna die.

31:26.840 --> 31:27.920
Right here.

31:36.840 --> 31:38.640
I would've buried you all

31:41.520 --> 31:43.600
but my mother, she, uh,

31:43.680 --> 31:45.680
she knows you, she said.

31:48.120 --> 31:50.760
It'll be worse for you
if I let you live

31:53.360 --> 31:55.520
and take away everything
that you have.

32:03.200 --> 32:04.440
Search him.

32:14.400 --> 32:16.840
Especially don't trust this bitch.

32:41.920 --> 32:42.960
So.

32:46.480 --> 32:47.520
Sign.

32:48.800 --> 32:50.680
Every fucking one of them.

32:57.280 --> 32:59.280
You can sign them on your knees.

33:01.080 --> 33:02.320
On the floor.

33:13.120 --> 33:16.800
Get on your fucking knees and sign.

33:20.520 --> 33:22.120
A friend of mine once said...

33:23.160 --> 33:25.320
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

33:25.400 --> 33:27.120
Big fucks small.

33:28.440 --> 33:30.440
So I had to find someone
bigger than you.

33:31.960 --> 33:35.080
Now, you may know there are
two families in Brooklyn,

33:35.160 --> 33:36.680
who want take over your monopoly

33:36.760 --> 33:38.960
on the import of liquor
into New York.

33:39.040 --> 33:41.840
But if they move against you
in New York,

33:41.920 --> 33:44.240
they'll start a war
between the families.

33:45.800 --> 33:49.840
But if you were to die in a vendetta

33:49.920 --> 33:52.840
with some fucking bookmaker
in Birmingham,

33:53.800 --> 33:55.840
they could take over your business
without a war.

33:57.880 --> 34:01.120
We also contacted
a businessman in Chicago.

34:05.000 --> 34:09.160
He's also interested in moving into
the liquor business in New York.

34:10.440 --> 34:12.120
His name is Alphonse Capone.

34:15.360 --> 34:17.320
You been talking to that fat fuck?

34:18.280 --> 34:20.360
You see, all the blood relatives
you brought with you

34:20.440 --> 34:24.600
from New York, they're all dead,
Mr Changretta.

34:24.680 --> 34:26.800
And these men here,

34:26.880 --> 34:29.160
they work for money,
for the highest bidder.

34:30.120 --> 34:31.760
They now have new orders.

34:33.760 --> 34:34.960
LUCA: Is that right?

34:40.240 --> 34:41.640
Is that right?

34:45.520 --> 34:47.360
And you, Matteo?

35:03.680 --> 35:04.760
Hey.

35:06.120 --> 35:07.520
Very fucking...

35:08.880 --> 35:09.960
(GRUNTING)

35:43.040 --> 35:45.920
TOMMY: <i>Arthur's been injured
but he's all right, Poll.</i>

35:48.240 --> 35:51.400
<i>We need to make them believe
that he's dead.</i>

35:53.720 --> 35:57.920
<i>To everyone but you, me, and Linda,</i>

35:58.520 --> 36:00.600
<i>Arthur Shelby is dead.</i>

36:02.720 --> 36:04.200
<i>I've got it all worked out.</i>

36:04.920 --> 36:07.880
<i>We can use his death to win this war.</i>

36:16.200 --> 36:17.280
(THUDS)

36:19.320 --> 36:22.840
(EXHALES DEEPLY)
Tell your people in Chicago

36:22.920 --> 36:25.040
that Michael Gray

36:25.120 --> 36:27.640
will sign the import
licence to New York.

36:27.720 --> 36:30.400
300 barrels of English dry gin
a month.

36:32.160 --> 36:33.160
Leave.

36:33.920 --> 36:34.920
All of ya.

36:38.080 --> 36:40.080
Tell your boss what you saw
here today.

36:40.840 --> 36:42.120
And tell him...

36:45.120 --> 36:47.440
You don't fuck with
the Peaky Blinders.

36:53.840 --> 36:55.840
(MUSIC PLAYING)

36:56.960 --> 36:58.960
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

37:10.640 --> 37:12.120
TOMMY: Nice. Hey!

37:13.200 --> 37:14.680
(CLEARS THROAT) Listen up. Um.

37:15.440 --> 37:18.600
Before we go and eat,
I'd like to say a few words.

37:20.040 --> 37:21.520
Last time we were all here,

37:23.600 --> 37:24.720
it ended badly.

37:25.480 --> 37:26.480
Yeah.

37:27.440 --> 37:29.000
And now, we're in a happier place.

37:32.520 --> 37:35.800
That's it.
I'd just like to raise a toast.

37:36.520 --> 37:37.680
Hold on.

37:38.320 --> 37:40.520
A few words I want to say
from the heart,

37:40.600 --> 37:42.240
and this time,

37:42.320 --> 37:44.280
you're gonna let me finish, Tommy.

37:44.360 --> 37:45.960
(CHATTERING)

37:46.040 --> 37:47.280
Now, as you all know,

37:48.480 --> 37:51.000
Arthur Shelby is dead.

37:52.080 --> 37:53.120
'Cause of that,

37:54.600 --> 37:56.160
Tommy's offered me a way out.

37:57.800 --> 37:59.080
A new identity.

38:00.280 --> 38:02.280
Start a whole new life for me self.

38:04.000 --> 38:05.280
I've thought about it.

38:08.040 --> 38:09.200
Made a decision.

38:13.680 --> 38:15.600
I ain't fucking going nowhere.

38:15.680 --> 38:17.680
(LAUGHING)

38:18.960 --> 38:21.080
Our enemies are gone.

38:21.160 --> 38:22.400
Dead, all of them.

38:25.000 --> 38:27.400
For the first time since me,

38:28.720 --> 38:29.960
my two kid brothers,

38:31.880 --> 38:33.400
Tommy and John,

38:35.360 --> 38:37.720
enlisted in the Warwickshire Yeomanry,

38:40.680 --> 38:41.760
we have peace.

38:43.960 --> 38:45.000
So.

38:46.080 --> 38:48.040
I think I'd like to make a proposal

38:50.000 --> 38:52.320
to all of you,
the Shelby Company Limited,

38:53.120 --> 38:56.240
insist that Tommy here

38:57.480 --> 38:58.960
take some time off.

39:00.640 --> 39:02.200
Time you took a holiday, Tom.

39:03.320 --> 39:04.480
Put your feet up.

39:05.760 --> 39:06.880
War's over.

39:07.520 --> 39:08.960
No one wants to kill us.

39:10.160 --> 39:11.320
To peace.

39:12.160 --> 39:13.800
ALL: To peace.

39:13.880 --> 39:14.960
(GLASSES CLINKING)

39:41.280 --> 39:43.280
I do hope you're gonna leave the dog
out of this.

39:44.920 --> 39:46.200
You were easy to find.

39:46.800 --> 39:48.680
Yeah, well there's a good reason
for that, Tommy.

39:49.680 --> 39:51.040
Because I wanted it to be here.

39:55.560 --> 39:56.960
I once told you, Alfie,

39:58.280 --> 40:00.680
that for business reasons
or in bad blood,

40:01.360 --> 40:02.520
I would kill you.

40:04.440 --> 40:06.240
I have no business reasons.

40:07.360 --> 40:09.360
It seems you have retired.

40:10.640 --> 40:13.440
So this is all purely for bad blood,
is it, Tommy?

40:13.520 --> 40:15.120
-Yeah.
-Right. Yeah.

40:15.720 --> 40:16.880
Told you.

40:17.840 --> 40:19.280
I wanted it to be here.

40:21.120 --> 40:23.200
-You gonna look after this dog?
-No.

40:23.760 --> 40:25.800
Right then. Well, his name is Cyril

40:25.880 --> 40:27.560
and he'll be very upset
and distressed,

40:27.640 --> 40:29.400
so you'll need to find him someone.

40:30.560 --> 40:32.320
-You're not armed?
-No.

40:33.400 --> 40:34.600
Don't be daft.

40:35.800 --> 40:37.760
The only thing I got on me

40:38.800 --> 40:40.400
is fucking cancer, mate.

40:45.200 --> 40:46.320
Yeah.

40:47.520 --> 40:48.720
Riddled with it.

40:49.640 --> 40:52.840
Doctor told me I might have picked it up
in France in the gas or something.

40:53.920 --> 40:55.400
He even showed me a photograph...

40:55.480 --> 40:57.360
Alfie, stop talking.

40:57.440 --> 40:59.880
So I said, "Margate" right,
and here I am.

40:59.960 --> 41:01.600
-Come on, Tommy.
-Alfie, look at me.

41:01.680 --> 41:04.280
There's an hon our able reason now
to pull that trigger...

41:04.360 --> 41:05.840
Alfie, look at me.

41:05.920 --> 41:08.200
Fucking get on with it.
Stop acting like a little girl.

41:08.280 --> 41:10.640
-Alfie!
-(GUNSHOTS)

42:48.040 --> 42:54.680
<i># Jumped in the river,
what did I see?</i>

42:57.160 --> 43:02.760
<i># Black.eyed angels swam with me</i>

43:02.840 --> 43:04.240
(EXPLOSION)

43:06.200 --> 43:08.680
<i>-# A moon full of stars and astral cars</i>
-(GUNSHOTS)

43:08.760 --> 43:10.760
(MEN SHOUTING)

43:14.280 --> 43:15.800
(DOGS BARKING)

43:15.880 --> 43:20.040
<i># And all the figures I used to see</i>

43:24.360 --> 43:31.320
<i># All my lovers were there with me</i>

43:33.640 --> 43:40.120
<i># All my past and futures</i>

43:40.200 --> 43:41.760
FRANCES: Mr Shelby.

43:44.480 --> 43:45.960
Mr Shelby.

43:48.920 --> 43:50.320
Mr Shelby.

43:51.120 --> 43:57.400
<i># There was nothing to fear
and nothing to doubt</i>

43:59.960 --> 44:02.800
Mr Shelby, you are not yourself.
I should call a doctor.

44:07.280 --> 44:08.880
It's all right, Frances.

44:10.480 --> 44:12.120
I'll call Mrs Gray.

44:13.840 --> 44:15.240
I know what this is...

44:16.960 --> 44:19.760
It's just myself talking to myself
about myself.

44:23.960 --> 44:25.640
Out. Thank you.

44:36.880 --> 44:43.800
<i># I jumped into the river</i>

44:46.040 --> 44:52.560
<i># Black.eyed angels swam with me</i>

44:55.080 --> 45:02.000
<i># A moon full of stars and astral cars</i>

45:03.560 --> 45:09.880
<i># And all the figures I used to see... #</i>

45:14.880 --> 45:16.240
(GLASS SHATTERS)

45:31.640 --> 45:33.040
Charlie.

46:09.240 --> 46:10.240
(CLEARS THROAT)

46:13.800 --> 46:15.360
Since I know you won't go yourself,

46:16.480 --> 46:18.200
I've been to a doctor on your behalf.

46:20.120 --> 46:22.280
No, it's all right.
None of the boys know you're sick.

46:27.240 --> 46:28.600
I'm not sick, Polly.

46:35.080 --> 46:37.520
It starts when you stop,
when you rest.

46:39.240 --> 46:40.440
Could be nerves.

46:42.320 --> 46:43.840
The war.

46:46.880 --> 46:49.640
It might be the alcohol.
Blue devils, they call that.

46:49.720 --> 46:50.920
Yeah, well. Yeah.

46:51.000 --> 46:52.280
Yeah, it's the fucking booze.

46:53.640 --> 46:56.400
It's the booze, the booze got out
and the booze got in me bones.

47:01.280 --> 47:02.600
Lizzie wants to see you.

47:02.920 --> 47:04.000
No.

47:04.400 --> 47:05.800
Tom, she's showing.

47:05.880 --> 47:07.280
I don't want to see Lizzie, Poll.

47:14.600 --> 47:16.360
Shit. Maybe it's in us.

47:19.760 --> 47:20.920
It's with Shelbys.

47:23.640 --> 47:25.160
It's in our Gypsy blood.

47:27.480 --> 47:29.600
We live somewhere
between life and death,

47:31.520 --> 47:33.080
waiting to move on.

47:36.120 --> 47:37.320
And in the end,

47:38.400 --> 47:39.560
we accept it.

47:42.280 --> 47:43.960
We shake hands with devils

47:45.400 --> 47:46.920
and we walk past them.

48:43.240 --> 48:45.000
Mr Shelby, you're meant to be resting.

48:47.920 --> 48:49.680
I've learned something, Frances.

48:51.760 --> 48:54.120
There's no rest for me in this world.

48:58.400 --> 48:59.680
Perhaps in the next.

49:08.160 --> 49:11.000
Them there, you pay out.
This one, you have to think.

49:11.080 --> 49:12.640
Use your fucking head, man.

49:12.720 --> 49:14.080
Right, even money.

49:14.160 --> 49:16.560
Whose fucking idea was it
that I go on holiday?

49:16.640 --> 49:20.040
Welcome back, Tommy. How was it?
What'd you get up to?

49:20.120 --> 49:21.520
Went fishing, played golf.

49:21.600 --> 49:22.960
Golf's fucking boring.

49:23.040 --> 49:24.160
Boring and easy.

49:24.240 --> 49:26.640
Yeah, well, what's the plan?

49:31.360 --> 49:33.400
TOMMY: <i>I need you to give
this to Jessie Eden.</i>

49:33.480 --> 49:34.760
<i>By hand.</i>

49:34.840 --> 49:36.560
-Yes, Mr Shelby.
-By your hand.

49:37.960 --> 49:40.080
This will be the last job
you'll do for me.

49:40.160 --> 49:42.040
You can go to Glasgow
and be with your family.

49:42.840 --> 49:43.840
You're free.

49:56.400 --> 49:58.000
You need to sign all of these.

50:08.720 --> 50:10.280
So you shook hands with the devil?

50:15.160 --> 50:16.200
Yeah.

50:17.720 --> 50:19.000
And I walked past him.

50:24.840 --> 50:25.840
Poll.

50:28.920 --> 50:30.160
I've had an idea.

50:31.720 --> 50:32.840
Oh, fuck.

50:39.760 --> 50:43.080
TOMMY: <i>"Dear Jessie,
now, more certainly than ever,</i>

50:43.240 --> 50:46.400
<i>"I believe things must change.
Things must change.</i>

50:47.160 --> 50:48.800
<i>"The general strike is holding.</i>

50:49.440 --> 50:50.920
<i>"We've not an hour to lose.</i>

50:51.680 --> 50:52.760
<i>"Meet me."</i>

51:03.800 --> 51:05.760
TOMMY: <i>I've made up my mind, Jessie.</i>
JESSIE: <i>About what?</i>

51:11.560 --> 51:13.320
Your cause is now my cause.

51:14.480 --> 51:15.560
I wanna help.

51:16.520 --> 51:19.280
The strike is holding. I want to meet
the people who can take this further.

51:21.360 --> 51:22.640
Are you serious?

51:23.280 --> 51:24.280
Yeah.

51:25.120 --> 51:26.240
I've done a lot of thinking.

51:28.080 --> 51:29.520
Right. I'll arrange a meeting.

51:30.400 --> 51:32.160
The operator knows my voice.

51:32.280 --> 51:33.480
Give me the name and the number.

51:41.160 --> 51:42.480
His name is Casey Douglas.

51:44.760 --> 51:46.600
It's Sparkhill 453.

51:46.680 --> 51:47.720
Right.

51:53.640 --> 51:55.040
And he's the leader of the cell?

51:58.480 --> 52:00.440
He's in contact with London
and Moscow.

52:03.520 --> 52:04.520
Good.

52:08.920 --> 52:10.560
Yeah. Sparkhill 453.

53:13.320 --> 53:15.520
BIGGE: <i>You are quite a creature,
Mr Shelby.</i>

53:17.440 --> 53:21.200
<i>When I received your note,
I wasn't sure you could deliver.</i>

53:26.600 --> 53:27.840
I've made contact

53:29.000 --> 53:32.040
with a Soviet agent inside
the Birmingham Communist Party.

53:35.040 --> 53:36.440
And do you have a name?

53:36.880 --> 53:39.840
And an address and a telephone number.

53:44.560 --> 53:46.040
I can be of great use to you.

53:47.880 --> 53:50.400
I can give you the name
of any communist party member,

53:51.360 --> 53:52.640
who is prepared to cross the line

53:52.720 --> 53:53.880
into armed revolution.

53:54.760 --> 53:57.240
We're in the fourth day
of a general strike,

53:57.320 --> 53:58.600
which appears to be holding.

53:59.800 --> 54:01.400
Even if it fails today,

54:02.640 --> 54:04.240
tomorrow they may succeed.

54:05.880 --> 54:06.880
Mmm.

54:09.720 --> 54:13.560
And you're offering to help ensure
they never succeed.

54:14.360 --> 54:15.640
If my cover is maintained,

54:16.880 --> 54:20.120
I can begin to shape the movement
and organise it myself.

54:21.240 --> 54:22.640
And undermine it?

54:23.600 --> 54:26.360
Rise through the ranks of the wider
Socialist movements.

54:29.440 --> 54:31.560
Of course.
You want something in return.

54:33.280 --> 54:35.720
What this time? A knighthood?

54:40.520 --> 54:41.680
My proposal.

54:43.520 --> 54:44.720
And my conditions.

54:48.760 --> 54:50.920
For the attention
of Winston Churchill?

54:51.560 --> 54:53.040
He holds me in very high regard.

55:01.240 --> 55:02.560
Are you serious?

55:03.480 --> 55:05.600
Breaking up a revolutionary cell
is one thing.

55:06.720 --> 55:09.200
Given my position of influence
in my home city.

55:10.240 --> 55:11.920
I could be of much more use
to you than that.

55:16.840 --> 55:21.040
<i># Where have you been
my blue.eyed son?</i>

55:22.920 --> 55:26.960
<i># And where have you been
my darling young one?</i>

55:29.040 --> 55:33.400
<i># I've stumbled on the side
of twelve misty mountains</i>

55:35.520 --> 55:40.200
<i># I've walked and I've crawled
on six crooked highways</i>

55:41.480 --> 55:46.160
<i># I've been ten thousand miles
in the mouth of a graveyard</i>

55:48.040 --> 55:51.040
<i># And it's a hard, and it's a hard</i>

55:51.120 --> 55:55.080
<i># And it's a hard, and it's a hard</i>

55:55.160 --> 56:01.000
<i># And it's a hard rain's gonna fall #</i>

56:01.080 --> 56:05.320
RETURNING OFFICER:
<i>Ronald Carr, Conservative, 3,412.</i>

56:05.400 --> 56:09.240
Bernard Hall, Liberal. 4,015.

56:09.320 --> 56:13.680
Michael Ross, Communist. 6,406.

56:13.760 --> 56:16.320
Thomas Shelby, Labour Party.

56:16.400 --> 56:19.200
48,564.

56:19.280 --> 56:21.280
(CROWD CHEERING AND APPLAUDING)

56:22.960 --> 56:24.960
I now declare Thomas Shelby

56:25.040 --> 56:27.120
to be the new
Labour Member of Parliament

56:27.200 --> 56:29.800
for the constituency
of Birmingham South.

56:31.200 --> 56:36.040
<i># I saw ten thousand talkers
whose tongues were all broken</i>

56:37.560 --> 56:41.040
<i># It's a hard, and it's a hard</i>

56:41.120 --> 56:44.720
<i># And it's a hard, and it's a hard</i>

56:44.800 --> 56:50.960
<i># It's a hard rain that's gonna fall #</i>

56:59.960 --> 57:01.960
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

57:16.160 --> 57:20.200
<i># On a gathering storm
comes a tall handsome man</i>

57:20.280 --> 57:24.960
<i># In a dusty black coat
with a red right hand #</i>

57:24.984 --> 57:29.984
http://hiqve.com/
